"'''Firepower'''" is a short story written by [[Carolyn Golledge]] (with illustrations by [[Doug Shuler]]) that was originally published in [[Star Wars Adventure Journal 8|''Star Wars Adventure Journal'' 8]] by [[West End Games]] in [[November]] [[1995]]. It was later made available online at [[Hyperspace: The Official Star Wars Fan Club|Hyperspace]] on [[May 12]], [[2006]].

==Plot summary==
After suffering repeated [[Starfighter/Legends|starfighter]] losses while raiding [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Imperial]] convoys, [[X-wing starfighter/Legends|X-Wing]] [[Squadron/Legends|squadron]] leader [[Stevan Makintay]] proposes recruiting sympathetic manufacturing experts as a way to alleviate [[Alliance to Restore the Republic/Legends|Rebel Alliance]] supply shortages. He undertakes a solo recruitment mission to his homeworld, [[Hargeeva]], a [[Planet/Legends|planet]] he fled as a [[Noble/Legends|noble]] in exile. His embittered betrothed, the [[Metallurgist|metallurgist]] [[Ketrian Altronel]], is at first resistant to his invitation, but when she witnesses the cruelty of the Empire firsthand, she has a change of heart. She and Mak are captured by the Empire and [[Shuttle/Legends|shuttled]] to [[Coruscant/Legends|Coruscant]] for interrogation. En route, their [[Transport/Legends|transport]] is waylaid by [[Pirate/Legends|pirates]], allowing Mak and Ketrian to avoid Imperial [[Prison/Legends|imprisonment]] and rejoin the Rebellion. Ketrain brings with her a breakthrough alloy that can increase the firepower of the Rebel X-Wings – but her [[Blood/Legends|veins]] carry a [[Poison/Legends|toxin]] injected by a nefarious Imperial, [[Nial Pedrin]], who wants her [[Death/Legends|dead]] before she can help the Rebellion.

